      • setWriteKey

        public Options.Builder setWriteKey​(String writeKey)
        WriteKey is the Honeycomb authentication token. If it is specified during LibHoney initialization, it will be used as the default write key for all events. If absent, write key must be explicitly set on a builder or event. Find your team write key at https://ui.honeycomb.io/account

        Default: None

        Parameters:
        writeKey - to set.

        this.

        public Options.Builder setDataset​(String dataset)
        Dataset is the name of the Honeycomb dataset to which to send these events. If it is specified during LibHoney initialization, it will be used as the default dataset for all events. If absent, dataset must be explicitly set on an EventFactory or Event.

        Default: None

      • setSampleRate

        public Options.Builder setSampleRate​(int sampleRate)
        SampleRate is the rate at which to sample this event. Default is 1, meaning no sampling. The probability of sending is 1/sampleRate. In other words, if one out of every 250 events is to be sent when Send() is called, you would specify set sample rate to 250.

        Must be greater than 1
        Default: 1

        Parameters:
        sampleRate - to set.
        Returns:
        this.
